From: Codex <noreply@openai.com>
Subject: [PATCH] mm: guard RTMM reclaim hooks with CONFIG_RTMM

The RTMM implementation is only linked when CONFIG_RTMM is enabled. Keep its
vmscan hooks under the same condition so configurations without RTMM link.
---
 mm/vmscan.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/vmscan.c b/mm/vmscan.c
--- a/mm/vmscan.c
+++ b/mm/vmscan.c
@@ -2368,3 +2368,5 @@ static void get_scan_count(struct lruvec *lruvec, struct mem_cgroup *memcg,
+#ifdef CONFIG_RTMM
 	if (unlikely(rtmm_reclaim(current->comm))) {
 		swappiness = rtmm_reclaim_swappiness();
 	}
+#endif
-- 
2.50.1
